# .ai — AI Assistant

This directory contains the AI skill library and orchestrator for this project.
It was set up by the [AI Skill Library](https://github.com/your-org/ai-skills-sample).

## How It Works

- **CLAUDE.md** (at project root) is the entry point for AI assistants
- **Skills** provide context-specific guidance (deployment, database, brand, etc.)
- **Orchestrator** enforces a structured workflow: discuss → plan → tasks → execute
- Skills are concise summaries — detail files are loaded on demand to save tokens

## Structure

```
.ai/
├── manifest.yaml              # Tracks which skill versions are active (git tracked)
├── lib/                       # Skill library (git clone, gitignored)
│   ├── skills/
│   │   ├── brand/skill.md
│   │   ├── deployment/skill.md
│   │   ├── database/skill.md
│   │   └── general/skill.md
│   ├── init.sh
│   └── migrate.sh
└── agent-execution/           # Ephemeral state (gitignored)
    ├── orchestrator.md        # Workflow definition
    ├── current-plan.md        # Active plan (created during work)
    └── tasks.md               # Task progress (created during work)
```

## Orchestrator Workflow

For non-trivial tasks, the AI follows this flow:

1. **DISCUSS** — Understand requirements, ask questions, confirm scope
2. **PLAN** — Write plan to `agent-execution/current-plan.md`, get user approval
3. **TASKS** — Break into checkable tasks in `agent-execution/tasks.md`
4. **EXECUTE** — Implement with progress tracking and resume capability
5. **REVIEW** — Verify, test, and present summary

If a conversation is interrupted, the AI resumes from the last unchecked task.

## Updating Skills

```bash
cd .ai/lib && git pull origin main && cd ../..
bash .ai/lib/migrate.sh
```

## Skill Versions

Current versions are tracked in `manifest.yaml`. Run `migrate.sh` to check for updates.
